<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,619,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="79">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is formed from the Latin noun 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Wang &amp; Guo &amp; Chen &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[900,967,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Sulcolotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis box="[900,967,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="79">ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to elytra with a long ovate black spot.
</paragraph>
